This file defines the main layout for the dashboard section of the application. It uses a flexbox container to arrange a sidebar and the main content area.

## Purpose

- To provide a consistent structural foundation for all pages within the `/dashboard` route.
- To ensure the sidebar is always visible and the main content area takes up the remaining space.

## Key Exports

- `default`: A React functional component that acts as the layout.

## Props

- `children`: A `React.ReactNode` representing the content that will be rendered within the main area of the dashboard.

## Usage

This layout is automatically applied to any page located within the `app/dashboard` directory. For example, `app/dashboard/page.tsx` will render its content within the `main` element of this layout.

```tsx
// Example of a page that would use this layout:
// app/dashboard/page.tsx

export default function DashboardHomePage() {
  return (
    <div>
      <h1>Welcome to the Dashboard!</h1>
      <p>This content is rendered within the main area of the dashboard layout.</p>
    </div>
  );
}
```
